{"itemid":1727,"subject":"One Alfie, Two Hugos","event":"John Joseph Adams was one of the winners at Sasquan.\r\n\r\nAs part of the LIGHTSPEED editorial team, he took home a Hugo for Best Semiprozine.\r\n\r\nBut he also won one of our Alfies as Best Editor, Short Form.  \r\n\r\nThough I searched for JJA in the aftermath of the Hugo ceremony in Spokane, I was never able to find him (he was in the bar, as it happens) to give him an invite to the Hugo Losers Party.  So he was not on hand to accept his trophy.\r\n\r\nWe shipped it to him instead.  It's finally turned up on his end, and he was kind enough to send a picture of the Alfie sandwiched between his two Hugos (from Sasquan and Loncon).\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/274309/274309_900.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"\">  \r\n\r\nThe Alfie doesn't have a name plate yet, you'll notice.  Since we had no way of knowing the winners until after the Hugo nominations were released, we could not get them engraved ahead of time.  But the plates are being engraved now, and will be shipped out shortly.\r\n\r\nJohn writes, \"The Alfie just arrived -- it looks so fabulous! Thanks again so so much! I've attached a picture of it in between my Hugos.  It's extra cool to win an Alfie for me -- THE STARS MY DESTINATION is my favorite book, and is kind of responsible for becoming an editor in the first place. I even invoked it in the opening of the foreword to volume one of BEST AMERICAN SCIENCE FICTION AND FANTASY.\"\r\n\r\n(( As an ironic footnote, Bester won his Hugo for THE DEMOLISHED MAN, though many people consider THE STARS MY DESTINATION his masterpiece.  Including me and John Joseph Adams, clearly.  However, the year that THE STARS MY DESTINATION would have been eligible, worldcon was in London, and for reasons incomprehensible to me <i><b>they dropped the Best Novel category</b></i>.  So Alfie was a Hugo loser too, and in a unique manner. ))\r\n\r\nAnyway, John, congrats, and thanks for sending the picture.","ditemid":442237,"eventtime":"2015-09-12 21:25:00","props":{"current_mood":"pleased","current_location":"Santa Fe","taglist":"alfies, hugo awards","current_moodid":109,"homepage_reposted":63986505,"commentalter":1443040498,"opt_lockcomments":1,"crosspost_tw":"One Alfie, Two Hugos http://goo.gl/XdWDF8","picture_keyword":"thumbs up","opt_screening":"F","revnum":2,"interface":"web","personifi_tags":"nterms:yes","langs":"{\"languages\":[[\"eng\",0.690716926120756]],\"detector\":\"Lingua-YALI:0.015\",\"updated\":1441941956}","revtime":1443053032},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2015-09-11 03:25:28","anum":125,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html","event_timestamp":1442093100,"reply_count":18,"comments":[{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/117822972/50679305","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22603901#t22603901","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22603901#t22603901","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22603901#t22603901","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1275181","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/jason.mellott.5","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22603901,"talkid":88296,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22603901#t22603901","upictitle":"Jason Mellott: pic#117822972","article":"They... dropped the best novel category? That makes absolutely no sense to me. Out of curiosity, what would have been eligible that year besides The Stars My Destination (which by the way I have started reading 2 days ago).<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 03:31:00 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/jason.mellott.5","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Jason Mellott","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1275181","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=50679305&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Jason Mellott","ctime_ts":1441942260,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/96744317/4545815","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604669#t22604669","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604669#t22604669","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604669#t22604669","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"kevin_standlee","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22604669,"talkid":88299,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604669#t22604669","above":22603901,"upictitle":"Kevin Standlee: Hugo Logo","article":"In the early days of the Hugo Awards, the categories were decided by the individual Worldcon committees. It wasn't until the 1960s that something recognizably like what we have today, with the members of Worldcon, through the Business Meeting, deciding what the categories should be and how the Awards should be administered.<br /><br />The <a href=\"http://www.thehugoawards.org/hugo-history/1957-hugo-awards/\">1957 Hugo Awards</a> in London, with only three categories (all of them for magazines: Fanzine, British Prozine, and American Prozine), were particularly strange in this free-form period.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 04:25:12 UTC","parent":22603901,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"kevin_standlee","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"kevin_standlee","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://kevin-standlee.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"kevin_standlee","ctime_ts":1441945512,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605693#t22605693","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605693#t22605693","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605693#t22605693","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"po8crg","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://po8crg.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22605693,"talkid":88303,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605693#t22605693","above":22604669,"upictitle":"po8crg: pic#0","article":"That makes me very tempted to suggest allowing retro-Hugos for years that had particularly thin years for categories.  But I think that would be just 1957.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 09:00:09 UTC","parent":22604669,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://po8crg.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"po8crg","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"po8crg","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://po8crg.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"po8crg","ctime_ts":1441962009,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/109399811/25292677","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22609789#t22609789","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22609789#t22609789","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22609789#t22609789","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"questron","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://questron.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22609789,"talkid":88319,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22609789#t22609789","above":22605693,"upictitle":"questron: Geek","article":"Well wouldn't not giving out a novel, novella OR short fiction award basically mean the spirit of the \"if a world con did not give out Hugos\" rule would apply if maybe not the exact wording?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 12 2015, 23:00:32 UTC","parent":22605693,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://questron.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"questron","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"questron","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://questron.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"questron","ctime_ts":1442098832,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/46721543/2854335","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604925#t22604925","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604925#t22604925","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604925#t22604925","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"kalimac","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://kalimac.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22604925,"talkid":88300,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22604925#t22604925","upictitle":"Kalimac: puzzle","article":"I have a theory, or maybe a hypothesis, as to why there was no Best Novel Hugo in 1957.  The International Fantasy Award, which was a juried award that was <i>also</i> shaped like a rocketship, was being presented at a banquet elsewhere in London the day after the Worldcon.  It was an invitational event, not officially part of the Worldcon, but many Worldcon members attended.<br /><br />My theory is that the Worldcon committee, knowing this, didn't feel that a Best Novel Hugo was necessary.  That would be an odd decision today, but remember that at that time the Hugos were not firmly established, they had much less prestige than the IFA, and awards were few and the overlap and duplication we're used to today were unknown.<br /><br />The book that received the IFA that year?  Tolkien's <i>The Lord of the Rings.</i>","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 04:32:19 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://kalimac.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"kalimac","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"kalimac","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://kalimac.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"kalimac","ctime_ts":1441945939,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605181#t22605181","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605181#t22605181","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605181#t22605181","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"loco73","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://loco73.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22605181,"talkid":88301,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605181#t22605181","upictitle":"loco73: pic#0","article":"Congratulations on this. I was wondering how come there aren't more nominations and awards for Ty Frank and Daniel Abraham and their fantastic series of novels comprising 'The Expanse\" saga!<br /><br />Their novels and novellas are simply put, some of the best books in recent memory, at least for me!!! These books are just outstanding. A space opera epic with both brains and brawn, fuel for the imagination. <br /><br />It has been due to works like \"A Song Of Ice And Fire\", \"The Expanse\", \"The Wheel Of Time\", \"The King Killer Chronicle\" and others, that my love for reading has remained intact, especially during a day and age when there are soo many distractions.<br /><br />I sincerely hope that in the near future their work gets the richly deserved recognition they should be welcomed to! ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 07:47:56 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Congrats!","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://loco73.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"loco73","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"loco73","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://loco73.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"loco73","ctime_ts":1441957676,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/122922956/1308823","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605437#t22605437","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605437#t22605437","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605437#t22605437","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"gerisullivan","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://gerisullivan.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22605437,"talkid":88302,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22605437#t22605437","upictitle":"Geri Sullivan: Geri 2014","article":"Sweet! Much as I join you in hoping the Alfies remain a one-shot, I think it's utterly fabulous that you created them.<br /><br />Just a few hours ago, I had the pleasure of watching video of Alfred Bester speaking in honor of Robert Heinlein during the GoH Banquet at MidAmeriCon. It was part of the initial tests we're doing on the project to digitize the Worldcon material in the Scott Imes Video Archive. There's more to come: the inventory includes a tape of Ro Nagy interviewing Bester. <br /><br />And, yes, I'll mention that you acquitted yourself very well on the Neo-Pro Workshop with Bob Tucker, Kirby McCauley, Ben Bova, and Sharon Jarvis at that same Worldcon. When we have a version small enough to put on a stick, I'll send it your way. (The archive files are running just over 100GB/hour, so those won't be showing up on YouTube anytime soon.)<br /><br />We look forward to sharing the 1976 videos at MidAmeriCon II next August!","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 08:53:36 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://gerisullivan.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"gerisullivan","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"gerisullivan","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://gerisullivan.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"gerisullivan","ctime_ts":1441961616,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/125400422/76791828","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22606205#t22606205","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22606205#t22606205","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22606205#t22606205","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_3300865","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://plus.google.com/105150876134948356105","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":22606205,"talkid":88305,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/442237.html?thread=22606205#t22606205","upictitle":"Winterstark: pic#125400422","article":"If you were to make a standardized Alfie statue, this particular one would be very appropriate because it looks almost exactly like the letter A in <b>Glagolitic, a medieval Slavic script</b> (http://glagoljica.stin.hr/index.php?menu=110&amp;action=3) that is no longer used. A for Alfie and all that.<br /><br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"1 year ago","ctime":"September 11 2015, 10:56:40 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Alfie statue","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://plus.google.com/105150876134948356105","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/google-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"